Sentencas: The possibility of fabricating large-area solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) with thin film electrolyte using a commercial physical vapor deposition technology is investigated.
Titulo: Scale-up of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Electrolyte

Sentencas: Yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ)/gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) bilayer electrolyte is successfully deposited on a 10 x 5 cm(2) commercial NiO/YSZ anode support by reactive magnetron sputtering.
Titulo: Scale-up of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Electrolyte

Sentencas: The microstructure of the fuel cells was studied by scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Scale-up of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Electrolyte

Sentencas: Current-voltage characteristics of fuel cells at a temperature of 750 degrees C and their power stability under electrical load were investigated.
Titulo: Scale-up of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Electrolyte

Sentencas: Single cells with La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3/ Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (LSCF/GDC) cathode had an open cell voltage of 1.14 V and a maximum power density of 490 mW cm(-2) at 750 degrees C using H-2/N-2 gas mixture as fuel and air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Scale-up of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Electrolyte

Sentencas: Three-cell planar SOFC stack using 10 x 5 cm(2) anode-supported unit cells with power density of 450 mW cm(-2) at a voltage of 0.7 V per cell has been assembled and tested.
Titulo: Scale-up of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Electrolyte
